content: Hello everyone! welcome to Online Renju Class.

The latest news in the world of Renju is the result of Japanese Meijin tournament.
That is the tournament where 10 strong Japanese will play in round robin,
and the winner of that tournament will have the match with the current champion of Japan.
The winner of the tournament this time was Mr Kazuto Hasegawa,
Do you know who is Japan champion now?
I know the name in Chinese,:)
So, soon we will see the match between these two players.
we will analysis some of the games from the tournament?
Mr Nakamura was absent this time again.
He did not join the Meijin tournament.
Mr Nakamura was a champion 2 years ago,
and then he did not accept the challenge of last year,
and therefore two best of meijin tournament played the final match last year.
I wasn't born in renju world at that time
I ask you, who were the two players who played the last meijin match?
since Hasegawa won the tournament just now,
we will mark this event by studying the game of last meijin match,

if Yamaguchi opened the game, he would play i3.

good block upside, but still opened for white down

We will now see how the game went on.

Before, ermine, ushi, dittp, Southerner, Don, Alan, sosei, Chaos, yzhnie, luwenzhe, jamphen, shuwang, Intotherenju, Jasny_sokol, smallpig, leto, yyfcsd, dhalsim, Malaj, coco_yuang, shai1144, renjunewbie, whte, concord2497, weigui, zjjwf, virag, fallnavy, Ikon, dadisheng, tieuphilac, lingdodo, johanna, wetcat, pantrike.
he did not have the patience of yy
He was too eager to win.
Well, it still looks that white is good here.
All of the sudden, black decided to bring up some activity.
What was the idea of black attack?
Actually, he knew he cannot win
in order to create potential fours
eliminate the future white development in right side and then turn to defence mainly in left sideyes
this black blocks the counta four
it was obvious that black cannot play there,
and sooner or later white takes it
so black prepared the counter-attack material so that when white gets f10, then black can get TWO defenses in a row -
one is e8, and then one more, thanks to the VCF threat
Now, the next couple of moves followed the Go-game tactics,
where both sides try to defend in the maximum benefit of their own space
this 30 is the best defense here,
because its closest to white area
Black in its turn used his area power, to weaken white's diagonal
and then black calmed down the position.
This is the first peaceful moment since the opening.
How do we evaluate the positition here?
white still has plenty of place to develop on the left
there's no way for black to continue go style, so it has to defend
any comment on the situation here on board?
I think white is a little better
34-D11 is a fairly good attack for white
balance now,but white has tempo,so w is better.
white has some activity in up-left corner, but little dangerous to black, and black can develop more freely than white
thank you very much. All of your comments were great!
if it was me i will play D11.
and you were all correct too
thanks to the defensive fours of h13 etc
Therefore Mr Yamaguchi played c10 first
Were I it,i would play d11
And white position looks still good.
Perhaps it was wise to balance a bit,
keeping white potential for future attacks on both left and right sides,
one can attack the whole game
But great Yamaguchi made a big mistake here
he was too eager to win
by making additional inner stone for white
assuming black has to block white's 4x3 at g12
and it turned out that there was no white win in uerr side
and that resulted with much weakened position for white
not only no win, but also seems has nothing
Now, white had lost a big chance to have safe and happy attack in lower side,
and that was a tactical mistake
Having seen the failure of move 38,
Yamaguchi maybe wanted so hard to make up the lost power,
and tried to attack from move 44.
It was a good fighting move,
and I admire his great fighting spirit,
as you see, white has the tempo
and black has some good space
we must consider the usage of tempo
if we cannot make good use for ourselves,
we should consider the defense right away,
otherwise after one poor attack of our own, we may end up in position where the defense is hopeless
it was possible to calm the position first
Maybe he expected black to be active
and enjoy the potential on the right
did the white's attack make the white position better or worse?
so the great potential is there
and black has good inner stone 47
I think white still can balance the pattern
and stone 53 supports black also in horizontal direction.
white can't push forbidden 6 fpr black?
As you see, the same upper fours, have so relevant role of support in the whole game for black
so, you can see why the 21 and 23 and 25 were so good.
but 58-i4, may be black still can not attack freely
no matter how white attack, it must turn to defence at left and lower side at last, and that's terrible.
So, now I want to tell you one important tactics:
the tactics that even top players often miss
when you are trying to make "best" defense,
so we will have new tactics lessons? in future?
you often use the most "outside" defense,
assuming it is enough for defense.
But the good player should foresee the coming battle.
it was obvious that regardless of the location of 32,
whether the stone 32 has any use for white in upper side
that the white stone 32, although so nicely outside, was useless.
and the top player would consider the long term planning,
and assume the j14 will be bothersome through m11
the m-line freedom is important for white in the future
the medium and strong player will play g14
and the champion will play j14
medium and strong player looks upper and left side
and champion looks upper left and right side
RT means yamakuchi is not champion
I dont mean Yamaguchi is not champion,
he just didnt make best move
most of you are in the level of g14-style now
its pretty hard to predict all this
but i feel some of you will soon reach the j14 champion thinkingf
Lets now see how it all ended.
Yamaguchi, having lose the hope to win as white,
Black created the VCF threat there
so white had to block the VCF
and the space on the left that existed long time ago,
and white has lost the tempo.
it is just what we predicted before move 44
now, black can enjoy the earned tempo
Mr Hasegawa didnt have difficulty to attack here.
should be easy for their level
its pretty difficult for me currently
white attempted the cut of VCF
does white have a VCF threat of its own now?
and Mr Hasegawa did not let his opponent confuse him,
